    <string name="termux_permission_required">Grant the Termux run-command permission, then tap setup again.</string>
    <string name="termux_permission_granted">Termux command permission is already granted.</string>
    <string name="termux_permission_denied">Permission denied. Open this app permissions and enable “Run commands in Termux environment”.</string>
    <string name="termux_overlay_required">Enable “Display over other apps” for Termux, then return and tap setup again.</string>
    <string name="termux_help">Termux setup:\n\nThere are two different permissions:\n\n1. Android Builder needs “Run commands in Termux environment”. This belongs to Android Builder, not Termux. Tap “Request Termux command permission” if you cannot find it in system settings. On some OPPO/ColorOS devices this custom permission is hidden; use the ADB permission command fallback.\n\n2. Termux needs “Display over other apps” so it can start terminal sessions from the background.\n\nTermux itself cannot be silently installed on normal Android. First install Termux, open it once, then enable external commands:\n   mkdir -p ~/.termux\n   echo allow-external-apps=true >> ~/.termux/termux.properties\nRestart Termux.\n\nAfter that, tap Run Termux Setup. The Copy buttons are fallback options.</string>
    <string name="third_party_notices_body">Android Builder includes an embedded runtime integration point designed for GPLv3-compatible Termux components.\n\nTermux app: GPLv3-only. Source: https://github.com/termux/termux-app\nTermux packages: https://github.com/termux/termux-packages\nterminal-emulator and terminal-view notices must be preserved if their code is bundled.\n\nIf this APK is distributed with Termux GPLv3 code or binaries, distribute the corresponding source code, license text, copyright notices, and any local modifications under GPLv3 terms.\n\nThe embedded backend creates a private runtime layout under files/runtime. Bootstrap zip layout may contain usr/bin, usr/android-sdk, home, or direct bin/android-sdk entries; they are installed into the private runtime.</string>
